  "body": "Saw this in some code and got to thinking about crafting some domain specific types\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n/// The size of a validators deposit in GWei.\r\npub const DEPOSIT_GWEI: u64 = 32_000_000_000;\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe can do something like\r\n```rust\r\nstruct GWei(u64);\r\n```\r\n\r\nto get type-safety where we know we want units of Gwei.\r\n\r\nThe downside is ergonomics as now we either need to implement some number of traits (e.g. `std::ops::{Add,...}` or have a bunch of manual wrapping/unwrapping to do...\r\n\r\nFigured I would bring this up for discussion...",
